      "abstract": unescape('Objective%3a%20To%20investigate%20whether%20affective%20and%20relational%20components%20of%20nurses%27%20experience%20of%20work%20have%20a%20significant%20impact%20on%20their%20intentions%20to%20leave%20either%20the%20job%20or%20the%20nursing%20profession%20in%20models%20that%20control%20for%20other%20factors%20%28sociodemographic%2c%20work%20conditions%2c%20perceptions%20of%20quality%20of%20care%29%20that%20are%20known%20to%20affect%20career%20decisions%2e%20Method%3a%20An%20exploratory%2c%20cross%2dsectional%20postal%20survey%20of%202880%20nurses%20in%20grades%20A%2013I%20in%2020%20National%20Health%20Service%20%28NHS%29%20Hospital%20Trusts%2c%2011%20in%20inner%20London%20and%20nine%20in%20outer%20London%2c%20was%20carried%20out%20between%20January%20and%20July%202002%2c%20looking%20at%20nurses%27%20intention%20to%20leave%20their%20current%20job%20or%20the%20nursing%20profession%2e%20The%20data%20were%20analysed%20using%20logistic%20regression%20with%20robust%20standard%20errors%2e%20Results%3a%20In%20models%20that%20controlled%20for%20known%20sources%20of%20job%20dissatisfaction%2c%20relationships%20with%20supervisors%20and%20managers%20were%20found%20to%20have%20a%20significant%20effect%20on%20respondents%27%20career%20intentions%2e%20Feeling%20valued%20by%20the%20Trust%20and%20by%20society%20was%20very%20important%2e%20Nurses%20seemed%20to%20distinguish%20between%20local%20problems%20that%20are%20the%20responsibility%20of%20the%20Trust%20and%20those%2c%20such%20as%20levels%20of%20pay%2c%20that%20could%20only%20be%20solved%20at%20the%20national%20level%2e%20Conclusion%3a%20Nurses%27%20career%20intentions%20are%20complex%20and%20multifactorial%2e%20Feelings%20of%20being%20valued%20and%20listened%20to%20play%20a%20role%2c%20as%20well%20as%20the%20individual%20and%20job%2drelated%20characteristics%2e%20The%20study%20highlights%20the%20role%20of%20supervisors%20and%20managers%20in%20retaining%20staff%20and%20suggests%20that%20investment%20in%20robust%20systems%20of%20communication%2c%20conflict%20resolution%20and%20security%20could%20slow%20nurse%20turnover%2e%20The%20NHS%20as%20an%20employer%20may%20be%20most%20interested%20in%20the%20role%20of%20pay%20in%20nurse%20retention%2c%20and%20the%20general%20public%20in%20how%20societal%20attitudes%20and%20verbal%20abuse%20shape%20nurses%27%20career%20decisions%2e'),
