      "abstract": unescape('Objectives%3a%20The%20current%20shortage%20of%20nurses%20is%20a%20major%20problem%20for%20health%20care%20systems%20around%20the%20world%20and%20has%20revitalized%20interest%20in%20the%20dynamics%20of%20nurses%27%20careers%2e%20This%20paper%20investigates%20the%20factors%20associated%20with%20qualified%20nurses%20in%20Britain%20moving%20to%20different%20employment%20statuses%2c%20including%20jobs%20outside%20nursing%2c%20unemployment%2c%20maternity%20leave%20and%20family%20care%20over%20time%2e%20Methods%3a%20British%20Household%20Panel%20Survey%20%28BHPS%29%20data%20collected%20between%201991%20and%202001%20were%20used%20to%20estimate%20the%20effects%20of%20covariates%20on%20transition%20rates%20between%20different%20employment%20statuses%2e%20Results%3a%20Individual%20characteristics%20associated%20with%20shorter%20tenure%20in%20the%20profession%20include%20being%20male%2c%20being%20younger%2c%20having%20a%20degree%2c%20and%20having%20been%20born%20in%20the%20UK%2e%20Many%20nurses%20leave%20to%20care%20for%20their%20families%2c%20which%20suggests%20the%20possibility%20of%20returning%20to%20the%20profession%20at%20a%20later%20date%2e%20A%20number%20of%20job%20characteristics%20are%20also%20related%20to%20leaving%2c%20including%20low%20pay%2c%20managerial%20responsibility%2c%20full%2dtime%20work%20and%20lack%20of%20opportunities%20to%20use%20initiative%2e%20Nurses%20seem%20to%20be%20particularly%20vulnerable%20to%20leaving%20early%20in%20their%20careers%2c%20but%20those%20who%20survive%20the%20first%20few%20years%20are%20likely%20to%20remain%20in%20the%20profession%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20their%20working%20lives%2e%20Conclusions%3a%20It%20is%20particularly%20important%20in%20policy%20terms%20that%20ability%20to%20use%20initiative%20is%20related%20to%20leaving%20nursing%20for%20another%20form%20of%20full%2dtime%20employment%20and%2c%20in%20particular%2c%20to%20leaving%20for%20a%20better%20job%2e%20This%20finding%20is%20consistent%20with%20results%20from%20studies%20of%20the%20Magnet%20hospitals%20in%20the%20US%2e%20Taken%20together%2c%20these%20results%20suggest%20that%20strategies%20to%20improve%20nurse%20retention%20must%20attend%20to%20nurses%27%20status%2c%20authority%20and%20position%20in%20the%20hierarchy%20if%20they%20are%20to%20be%20successful%2e%20The%20results%20also%20provide%20strong%20support%20for%20those%20who%20argue%20that%20better%20rates%20of%20pay%20are%20necessary%20in%20order%20to%20improve%20nurse%20retention%2e'),
