      "abstract": unescape('This%20paper%20presents%20the%20authors%27%20opinion%20on%20claims%20of%20Petersen%20and%20Koput%20%28PK%29%20regarding%20a%20problem%20in%20the%20usual%20interpretation%20of%20tests%20of%20the%20theory%20of%20density%2ddependent%20legitimation%20and%20competition%20as%20applied%20to%20rates%20of%20organizational%20mortality%2e%20PK%20argue%20that%20the%20negative%20first%2dorder%20effect%20of%20organizational%20density%20on%20mortality%20rates%20is%20compatible%20with%20a%20simpler%20and%20thus%20preferable%20alternative%20explanation%20that%20relies%20on%20the%20operation%20of%20unobserved%20heterogeneity%20instead%20of%20legitimation%2e%20Their%20strongly%20stated%20assertions%20of%20generality%20fail%20to%20acknowledge%20that%20the%20artifactual%20effect%20of%20density%20occurred%20in%20only%20half%20of%20their%20simulations%2e%20Even%20substantively%20trivial%20effects%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20statistically%20significant%20when%20so%20many%20observations%20are%20generated%20by%20the%20simulation%2e%20Age%20of%20population%20and%20density%20are%20so%20highly%20correlated%20in%20the%20data%20sets%20produced%20by%20the%20simulation%20structure%20of%20PK%20that%20we%20could%20not%20estimate%20models%20including%20these%20two%20variables%20because%20we%20could%20not%20invert%20the%20Hessian%2e%20The%20most%20unrealistic%20feature%20of%20the%20simulation%20of%20PK%20concerns%20its%20treatment%20of%20founding%20processes%2e%20For%20unexplained%20reasons%2c%20they%20chose%20a%20deterministic%20founding%20process%3a%20The%20same%20fixed%20number%20of%20foundings%20occur%20each%20year%20in%20each%20frailty%20class%2e'),
      "type": "article",
      "title": "On the Interpretation of Density Dependence in Rates of Organizational Mortality.(Reply to Petersen and Koput)",
